cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SOC

This paper discusses the development and use of bibliometric indicators in research evaluation and management, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as bibliometrics is a key area of research in this field. The paper also touches upon social aspects of bibliometrics, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the algorithmic aspects of bibliometric indicators, which could place it in cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
